st_frequent_category <- levels(Taxi$payment_type)[which.max(table(Taxi$payment_type))]\n\n# Step 2: Impute missing values with the most frequent category\nTaxi$payment_type[is.na(Taxi$payment_type)] <- most_frequent_category\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-08-22T17:02:31.563114Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-08-22T17:02:31.565064Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-08-22T17:02:31.599399Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":35,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Here's a short explanation of what we did in the code:**\n* We focused on the \"payment_type\" column, which was represented as integers.\n* To handle it as a categorical variable, we converted the column to a factor using the factor() function.\n* We then calculated the most frequent category (mode) from the levels of the factorized \"payment_type\" column.\n* After identifying the mode, we replaced missing values in the \"payment_type\" column with the calculated mode.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"> Let's verify if we have successfully handled missing values ","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"colSums(is.na(Taxi)) / rows * 100","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-08-22T17:05:06.158111Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-08-22T17:05:06.160085Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-08-22T17:05:06.201082Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":36,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/html":"<style>\n.dl-inline {width: auto; margin:0; padding: 0}\n.dl-inline>dt, .dl-inline>dd {float: none; width: auto; display: inline-block}\n.dl-inline>dt::after {content: \":\\0020\"; padding-right: .5ex}\n.dl-inline>dt:not(:first-of-type) {padding-left: .5ex}\n</style><dl class=dl-inline><dt>lpep_pickup_datetime</dt><dd>0</dd><dt>lpep_dropoff_datetime</dt><dd>0</dd><dt>PULocationID</dt><dd>0</dd><dt>DOLocationID</dt><dd>0</dd><dt>passenger_count</dt><dd>0</dd><dt>trip_distance</dt><dd>0</dd><dt>fare_amount</dt><dd>0</dd><dt>extra</dt><dd>0</dd><dt>mta_tax<